    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - Troubleshooting - Diagnostic Mode</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Diagnostic Mode</title>
        <para>To perform the test, proceed as follows:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unplug the controller.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and hold the ENTER button while plugging the cable back into the controller.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the ENTER button, then push each button once to light up from left to right
                (starting with the HEAT button).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After all buttons are pressed in the correct sequence, the controller will perform a
                self-check and beep (if working).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wait about 30s for the display to appear and adjust contrast if necessary (press and hold
                the ENTER button while turning the SCROLL DIAL counter clockwise).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The controller will now operate the condenser fan, enclosure fan and the radiator/heat
                exchanger fan for 30s (verify operation).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and hold the FAN button while turning the SCROLL DIAL to scroll through the operating
                parameters (displayed directly below the temperature setting).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unplug controller cable from the controller and plug back in to exit diagnostic mode.</para>
        </step1>
